The telephone rang in the back parlor. Mrs. Wylie excused herself to answer.
                    After a few words she closed the doors between. She was gone fully five minutes;
                    to Susan it seemed an hour. She came back, saying:

He rose. "Please let me have my way." And he led her to a bench across which a
                    tree threw a deep shadow; as they sat there, neither could see the other's face
                    except in dimmest outline. After a brief silence he began:
